portfolio and pipeline.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet important transactions,&#8221; said </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">Christopher Boerner, Ph.D.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">, board chair and chief executive officer, Bristol Myers Squibb. &#8220;Our focus remains on strengthening the company's long-term growth profile. As a part of our continued evolution, we're executing a strategic productivity initiative that will allow us to be more agile, drive efficiency across the company, and prioritize investing in opportunities where we see the greatest potential to get the most promising medicines to patients as quickly as possible.&#34;</font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">Bristol Myers Squibb posted first quarter revenues of $11.9 billion, an increase of 5% or 6% when adjusted for foreign exchange impacts, primarily driven by </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Eliquis</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Reblozyl </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Opdualag, </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">partially offset by</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Opdivo </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Revlimid.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">U.S. revenues increased 7% to $8.5 billion primarily due to </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Eliquis</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Reblozyl </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Opdualag,</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> partially offset by </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Revlimid. Opdivo </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">revenues were $1.2 billion compared to $1.3 billion, representing a decrease of 10% primarily due to inventory and the timing of orders, partially offset by demand growth.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">International revenues remained relatively flat at $3.4 billion primarily due to lower average net selling prices, offset in part by higher demand for </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Opdivo</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">, </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Yervoy </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Reblozyl</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">. The negative impact from foreign exchange was 5%.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, gross margin decreased from 77.4% to 75.3%, and on a non-GAAP basis, gross margin decreased from 77.8% to 75.5%, primarily due to product mix.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, marketing, selling and administrative expenses increased 34% to $2.4 billion and on a non-GAAP basis, increased 13% to $2.0 billion, primarily due to the timing of spend and the impact of recent acquisitions.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, research and development expenses increased 16% to $2.7 billion and on a non-GAAP basis, increased 6% to $2.3 billion, primarily due to the impact of recent acquisitions and higher costs to support the overall portfolio.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP and non-GAAP basis, Acquired IPRD increased to $12.9 billion from $75 million, primarily due to the Karuna asset acquisition and SystImmune collaboration. On a GAAP and non-GAAP basis, licensing income was $12 million compared to $43 million during the same period a year ago. </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, amortization of acquired intangible assets increased 4% to $2.4 billion, primarily due to the Mirati Therapeutics and RayzeBio acquisitions and approval of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Augtyro</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> in the fourth quarter of 2023.</font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, income tax expense was $392 million on a pre-tax loss of $11.5 billion and on a non-GAAP basis, income tax expense was $732 million on a pre-tax loss of $8.2&#160;billion primarily due to the $12.1 billion one-time, non-tax-deductible charge for the acquisition of Karuna.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On a GAAP basis, the company reported net loss attributable to Bristol Myers Squibb of $11.9&#160;billion, or ($5.89) per share, during the first quarter of 2024 compared to net earnings of $2.3&#160;billion, or $1.07 per share, for the same period a year ago. In addition to the items above, the decrease was also due to lower litigation and other settlement income. The company reported on a non-GAAP basis net loss attributable to Bristol Myers Squibb of $8.9&#160;billion, or ($4.40) per share, during the first quarter of 2024 compared to net earnings of $4.3&#160;billion, or $2.05 per share, for the same period a year ago. In addition to the items above, the decrease was also due to higher interest expense resulting from new debt issuance to fund recent acquisitions.</font></div><div Growth Portfolio revenues were primarily driven by higher demand for </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Reblozyl, Opdualag, Yervoy, Camzyos, </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Sotyktu, </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">partially offset by</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Opdivo </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">and</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> Abecma. </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:174%">Legacy Portfolio</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Revenues for the Legacy Portfolio in the first quarter were $7.1&#160;billion compared to $6.9&#160;billion in the prior year period. #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">approved</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Opdivo</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">, in combination with cisplatin and gemcitabine, for the first-line treatment of adult patients with unresectable or metastatic urothelial carcinoma (UC). The approval is based on results from the Phase 3 CheckMate -901 trial evaluating </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Opdivo</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Opdivo</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> monotherapy, compared to cisplatin-gemcitabine alone, for patients with previously untreated unresectable or metastatic UC.</font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"><div><font><br></font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt The FDA assigned a PDUFA goal date of October 8, 2024.</font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">In addition, the European Medicines Agency (EMA) validated the type II variation application for neoadjuvant Opdivo with chemotherapy followed by surgery and adjuvant </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Opdivo</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> for the perioperative treatment of resectable stage IIA to IIIB NSCLC. Application validation confirms the submission is complete and begins the EMA&#8217;s centralized review procedure. </font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The FDA&#8217;s sBLA acceptance and the EMA&#8217;s application validation are based on results from the Phase 3 CheckMate -77T trial.</font></div><div><font><br></font></div></td></tr></table></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">5</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:65.568%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Clinical &#38; Research</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">Krazati</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The pivotal </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">Phase 3 KRYSTAL-12 study</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">, evaluating </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Krazati</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> as a monotherapy in patients with pretreated locally advanced or metastatic NSCLC harboring a KRAS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">G12C</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> mutation, met the primary endpoint of progression-free survival (PFS) and the key secondary endpoint of overall response rate as assessed by Blinded Independent Central Review at final analysis for these endpoints. pre-treated patients. </font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> for the treatment of adult patients with relapsed and refractory multiple myeloma who have received at least two prior therapies, including an immunomodulatory agent, a proteasome inhibitor, and an anti-CD38 antibody and have demonstrated disease progression on the last therapy. The approval is based on results from the Phase 3 KarMMa-3 trial. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Abecma</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> is the first CAR T cell immunotherapy approved in the European Union for use in earlier lines of therapy for relapsed and refractory multiple myeloma. </font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">Abecma</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The FDA </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">approved</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Abecma</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> for the treatment of adult patients with relapsed or refractory multiple myeloma after two or more prior lines of therapy, including an immunomodulatory agent, a proteasome inhibitor, and an anti-CD38 monoclonal antibody. </font></div><div><font><br></font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"></td><td MS',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:115%"> (lisocabtagene maraleucel) </font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> accelerated approval of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet received at least two prior lines of therapy, including a Bruton tyrosine kinase inhibitor and a B-cell lymphoma 2 inhibitor. The accelerated approval is based on the Phase 1&#47;2 open-label, single-arm TRANSCEND CLL 004 trial.</font></div></td></tr></table></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">6</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:65.568%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Reblozyl</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174; </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">(luspatercept-aamt)</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The EC </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">expanded approval</font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Reblozyl </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">to include the first-line treatment of adult patients with transfusion-dependent anemia due to very low, low and intermediate-risk myelodysplastic syndromes. The approval covers all European Union member states and is based on the pivotal Phase 3 COMMANDS trial. </font></div></td></tr></table></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%">Immunology</font></div><div><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:15.566%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:65.568%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="background-color:#f2f2f2;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Category</font></td><td colspan="3" style="background-color:#f2f2f2;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Asset</font></td><td colspan="3" style="background-color:#fcf5da;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Milestone</font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Clinical &#38; Research</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">Zeposia</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174; </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">(</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">ozanimod)</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">First of two induction </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">Phase 3 YELLOWSTONE trials</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> evaluating </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Zeposia </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">in adult patients with moderate-to-severe active Crohn's disease did not meet its primary endpoint of clinical remission at Week 12. The safety profile of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Zeposia </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">in this study was consistent with that observed in previously reported trials. </font></div><div><font><br></font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">Zeposia</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Data from the </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">Phase 3 DAYBREAK</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> open-label extension trial demonstrated the long-term efficacy and safety profile of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Zeposia</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> in patients with relapsing forms of multiple sclerosis. In the DAYBREAK long-term extension study, treatment with </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Zeposia</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> demonstrated a low annualized relapse rate of 0.098 and 67% of patients were relapse-free at six years. An analysis of DAYBREAK data showed nearly 97% of followed patients were relapse-free at 90 days post </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Zeposia</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> discontinuation. Patients that did relapse showed no evidence of rebound effect.</font></div></td></tr></table></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font Research</font></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:115%">KarXT (xanomeline-trospium)</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="border-bottom:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-left:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-right:1pt solid #dbdbdb;border-top:1pt solid #dbdbdb;padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Interim long-term efficacy data from the </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">Phase 3 EMERGENT-4</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> open-label extension trial demonstrated that KarXT was associated with significant improvement in symptoms of schizophrenia across all efficacy measures at 52 weeks.  </font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">In addition, pooled interim long-term safety, tolerability and metabolic outcomes data from the </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%;text-decoration:underline">Phase 3 EMERGENT-4 and EMERGENT-5 trials</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> evaluating the safety, tolerability and efficacy of KarXT in adults with schizophrenia showed that KarXT demonstrated a favorable weight and long-term metabolic profile where most patients experience stability or improvements on key metabolic parameters over 52 weeks of treatment. KarXT was generally well-tolerated, with a side effect profile consistent with prior trials of KarXT in schizophrenia. </font></div><div><font><br></font></div></td></tr></table></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div id="iaa86aefc49b24f2eb4d89824601b3679_16"></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">Business Development</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">The company recently completed multiple transactions, strengthening its long-term growth profile and enhancing its portfolio and pipeline.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">With the </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">acquisition</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%"> of Karuna Therapeutics, Inc., Bristol Myers Squibb expanded its position in neuroscience and added important assets, including KarXT, an antipsychotic with a novel mechanism of action and differentiated efficacy and safety. KarXT has a PDUFA goal date of September 26, 2024, for the treatment of schizophrenia in adults. </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font bispecific antibody-drug conjugate with the potential to treat a variety of solid tumors, including lung and breast cancer.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">On April 22, Bristol Myers Squibb and Cellares </font><font As a part of the agreement, Cellares will optimize, automate, and tech-transfer select Bristol Myers Squibb CAR T cell therapies onto its automated and high-throughput manufacturing platform, the Cell Shuttle</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:7.8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;position:relative;top:-4.2pt;vertical-align:baseline">TM</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">. This agreement enables Bristol Myers Squibb to expand its manufacturing capacity, meeting the growing demand for its diverse range of cell therapies through a platform that is scalable and has the potential to improve turnaround time, bringing the promise of cell therapies to more patients faster.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div drive growth. </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">The 2024 financial guidance excludes the impact of any potential future strategic acquisitions,  divestitures, specified items that have not yet been identified and quantified, and the impact of future Acquired IPRD charges. To the extent we have quantified the impact of significant R&#38;D charges or other income resulting from upfront or contingent milestone payments in connection with asset acquisitions or licensing of third-party intellectual property rights, we may update this information from time to time on our website </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">www.bms.com</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">, in the &#34;Investors&#34; section. Non-GAAP guidance assumes current exchange rates. The financial guidance is subject to risks and </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">9</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">uncertainties applicable to all forward-looking statements as described elsewhere in this press release. </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">A reconciliation of forward-looking non-GAAP measures, including non-GAAP EPS, to the most directly comparable GAAP measures is not provided because comparable GAAP measures for such measures are not reasonably accessible or reliable due to the inherent difficulty in forecasting and quantifying measures that would be necessary for such reconciliation. Namely, we are not without unreasonable effort, able to reliably predict the impact of accelerated depreciation and impairment charges, legal and other settlements, gains and losses from equity investments and other adjustments. In addition, the company believes such a reconciliation would imply a degree of precision and certainty that could be confusing to investors. These items are uncertain, depend on various factors and may have a material impact on our future GAAP results. See &#34;Cautionary Statement Regarding Forward-Looking Statements&#34; and &#34;Use of Non-GAAP Financial Information.&#34;</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">Environmental, Social &#38; Governance (ESG)</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">As a leading biopharmaceutical company, Bristol Myers Squibb's passion for making an impact extends beyond the discovery, development and delivery of innovative medicines that help patients prevail over serious diseases.  </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:11.71pt">On April 2, 2024, the company published its latest </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">ESG report</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">, which details the company's meaningful progress, its evolved ESG strategy, and its long-term aspirational ESG goals. The company's evolved approach further integrates its ESG strategy and its business strategy. The ESG strategy focuses on three core pillars&#58; advancing patient health around the world, expanding the boundaries of science, and fostering a high-performing and inclusive global workforce.                                      </font></div><div style="text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Highlights from the report include&#58;</font></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#9702;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:13.75pt">Advancing tailored access programs in low-and middle-income countries&#59; </font></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#9702;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:13.75pt">Making clinical trials more accessible to underrepresented groups and ensuring research efforts better reflect patient populations&#59;</font></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#9702;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:13.75pt">Sustained workforce representation and increased community engagement by the company's employees&#59;</font></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#9702;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:13.75pt">Advancing climate action goals and increasing the company's renewable energy footprint&#59; and</font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">10</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">&#9702;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%;padding-left:13.75pt">Incorporating new ESG metrics into the executive compensation program and advancing data privacy and cybersecurity efforts.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div id="iaa86aefc49b24f2eb4d89824601b3679_19"></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">Conference Call Information</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:174%">Bristol Myers Squibb will host a conference call today, Thursday, April 25, 2024, at 8&#58;00 a.m. ET during which company executives will review quarterly financial results and address inquiries from investors and analysts. MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Use of Non-GAAP Financial Information </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">In discussing financial results and guidance, the company refers to financial measures that are not in accordance with U.S. Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP). The non-GAAP financial measures are provided as supplemental information to the financial measures presented in this press release that are calculated and presented in accordance with GAAP and are presented </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">11</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">because management has evaluated the company&#8217;s financial results both including and excluding the adjusted items or the effects of foreign currency translation, as applicable, and believes that the non-GAAP financial measures presented portray the results of the company's baseline performance, supplement or enhance management's, analysts' and investors' overall understanding of the company&#8217;s underlying financial performance and trends and facilitate comparisons among current, past and future periods. In addition, non-GAAP gross margin, which is gross profit excluding certain specified items, as a percentage of revenues, non-GAAP operating margin, which is gross profit less marketing, selling and administrative expenses and research and development expenses excluding certain specified items as a percentage of revenues, non-GAAP operating expenses, which is marketing, selling and administrative and research and development expenses excluding certain specified items, non-GAAP marketing, selling and administrative expenses, which is marketing, selling and administrative expenses excluding certain specified items, and non-GAAP research and development expenses, which is research and development expenses excluding certain specified items, are relevant and useful for investors because they allow investors to view performance in a manner similar to the method used by our management and make it easier for investors, analysts and peers to compare our operating performance to other companies in our industry and to compare our year-over-year results. </font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This earnings release and the accompanying tables also provide certain revenues and expenses as well as non-GAAP measures excluding the impact of foreign exchange (&#34;Ex-Fx&#34;). We calculate foreign exchange impacts by converting our current-period local currency financial results using the prior period average currency rates and comparing these adjusted amounts to our current-period results. Ex-Fx financial measures are not accounted for according to GAAP because they remove the effects of currency movements from GAAP results.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Non-GAAP financial measures such as non-GAAP earnings and related EPS information are adjusted to exclude certain costs, expenses, gains and losses and other specified items that are evaluated on an individual basis after considering their quantitative and qualitative aspects and typically have one or more of the following characteristics, such as being highly variable, difficult to project, unusual in nature, significant to the results of a particular period or not indicative of past or future operating results. These items are excluded from non-GAAP earnings and related EPS information because the company believes they neither relate to the ordinary course of the company&#8217;s business nor reflect the company&#8217;s underlying business performance. Similar charges or gains were recognized in prior periods and will likely reoccur in future periods, including amortization of acquired intangible assets, including product rights that generate a significant portion of our ongoing revenue and will recur until the intangible assets are fully amortized, unwind of inventory purchase price adjustments, acquisition and integration expenses, restructuring costs, accelerated depreciation and impairment of property, plant and equipment and intangible assets, costs of acquiring a priority review voucher, stock compensation resulting from acquisition-related equity awards, pension, legal and other contractual settlement charges, equity investment and contingent value rights fair value adjustments (including fair value adjustments attributed to limited partnership equity method investments), income resulting from the change in control of the Nimbus Therapeutics TYK2 Program and amortization of fair value adjustments of debt acquired from Celgene in our 2019 exchange offer, among other items. Deferred and current income taxes attributed to these items are also adjusted for considering their individual impact to the overall tax expense, deductibility and jurisdictional tax rates.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Because the non-GAAP financial measures are not calculated in accordance with GAAP, they should not be considered superior to and are not intended to be considered in isolation or as a substitute for the related financial measures presented in the press release that are prepared in accordance </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">12</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">with GAAP and may not be the same as or comparable to similarly titled measures presented by other companies due to possible differences in method and in the items being adjusted. We encourage investors to review our financial statements and publicly-filed reports in their entirety and not to rely on any single financial measure.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Reconciliations of the non-GAAP financial measures to the most comparable GAAP measures are provided in the accompanying financial tables and will also be available on the company&#8217;s website at www.bms.com. Within the accompanying financial tables presented, certain columns and rows may not add due to the use of rounded numbers. Percentages and earnings per share amounts presented are calculated from the underlying amounts.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">A reconciliation of forward-looking non-GAAP measures, including non-GAAP EPS, to the most directly comparable GAAP measures is not provided because comparable GAAP measures for such measures are not reasonably accessible or reliable due to the inherent difficulty in forecasting and quantifying measures that would be necessary for such reconciliation. Namely, we are not, without unreasonable effort, able to reliably predict the impact of accelerated depreciation and impairment charges, legal and other settlements, gains and losses from equity investments and other adjustments.  In addition, the company believes such a reconciliation would imply a degree of precision and certainty that could be confusing to investors. These items are uncertain, depend on various factors and may have a material impact on our future GAAP results.</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Website Information</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">We routinely post important information for investors on our website, BMS.com, in the &#8220;Investors&#8221; section. We may use this website as a means of disclosing material, non-public information and for complying with our disclosure obligations under Regulation FD. Accordingly, investors should monitor the Investors section of our website, in addition to following our press releases, Securities and Exchange Commission (&#34;SEC&#34;) filings, public conference calls, presentations and webcasts. We may also use social media channels to communicate with our investors and the public about our company, our products and other matters, and those communications could be deemed to be material information. The information contained on, or that may be accessed through, our website or social media channels are not incorporated by reference into, and are not a part of, this document.</font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Cautionary Statement Regarding Forward-Looking Statements</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Trebuchet MS',sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This earnings release and the related attachments (as well as the oral statements made with respect to information contained in this release and the attachments) contain certain &#8220;forward-looking&#8221; statements within the meaning of Section 27A of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, and Section 21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, regarding, among other things, the company&#8217;s 2024 financial guidance, plans and strategy, including its business development and capital allocation strategy, anticipated developments in the company&#8217;s pipeline, expectations with respect to the company&#8217;s future market position and the projected benefits of the company&#8217;s alliances and other business development activities. <DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Q1 2024 Results Not for Product Promotional Use Forward Looking Statements and Non-GAAP Financial Information  2 This presentation contains statements about Bristol-Myers Squibb Company&#8217;s (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) future financial results, plans, business development strategy, anticipated clinical trials, results  and regulatory approvals that constitute forward-looking statements for purposes of the safe harbor provisions under the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995.  All statements that  are not statements of historical facts are, or may be deemed to be, forward-looking statements.  Actual results may differ materially from those expressed in, or implied by, these statements as  a result of various factors, including, but not limited to: (i) new laws and regulations, (ii) our ability to obtain, protect and maintain market exclusivity rights and enforce patents and other  intellectual property rights, (iii) our ability to achieve expected clinical, regulatory and contractual milestones on expected timelines or at all, (iv) difficulties or delays in the development and  commercialization of new products, (v) difficulties or delays in our clinical trials and the manufacturing, distribution and sale of our products, (vi) adverse outcomes in legal or regulatory  proceedings, (vii) risks relating to acquisitions, divestitures, alliances, joint ventures and other portfolio actions and (viii) political and financial instability, including changes in general economic  conditions.  These and other important factors are discussed in the Company&#8217;s most recent annual report on Form 10-K and reports on Forms 10-Q and 8-K.  These documents are available on  the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission&#8217;s website, on the Company&#8217;s website or from Bristol-Myers Squibb Investor Relations.  No forward-looking statements can be guaranteed. In addition, any forward-looking statements and clinical data included herein are presented only as of the date hereof.  Except as otherwise required by applicable law, the Company undertakes  no obligation to publicly update any of the provided information, whether as a result of new information, future events, changed circumstances or otherwise. This presentation includes certain non-generally accepted accounting principles (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;) financial measures that we use to describe the Company&#8217;s performance.  The non-GAAP financial  measures are provided as supplemental information and are presented because management has evaluated the Company&#8217;s financial results both including and excluding the adjusted items or  the effects of foreign currency translation, as applicable, and believes that the non-GAAP financial measures presented portray the results of the Company&#8217;s baseline performance, supplement  or enhance management&#8217;s, analysts&#8217; and investors&#8217; overall understanding of the Company&#8217;s underlying financial performance and trends and facilitate comparisons among current, past and  future periods. This presentation also provides certain revenues and expenses excluding the impact of foreign exchange (&#8220;Ex-FX&#8221;). We calculate foreign exchange impacts by converting our  current-period local currency financial results using the prior period average currency rates and comparing these adjusted amounts to our current-period results.  Ex-FX financial measures are  not accounted for according to GAAP because they remove the effects of currency movements from GAAP results.  The non-GAAP information presented herein provides investors with additional useful information but should not be considered in isolation or as substitutes for the related GAAP measures.   Moreover, other companies may define non-GAAP measures differently, which limits the usefulness of these measures for comparisons with such other companies.  We encourage investors to  review our financial statements and publicly filed reports in their entirety and not to rely on any single financial measure.  An explanation of these non-GAAP financial measures and a  reconciliation to the most directly comparable financial measure are available on our website at www.bms.com/investors.  Also note that a reconciliation of forward-looking non-GAAP measures, including non-GAAP earnings per share (EPS), to the most directly comparable GAAP measures is not provided because  comparable GAAP measures for such measures are not reasonably accessible or reliable due to the inherent difficulty in forecasting and quantifying measures that would be necessary for such  reconciliation.  Namely, we are not, without unreasonable effort, able to reliably predict the impact of accelerated depreciation and impairment charges, legal and other settlements, gains and  losses from equity investments and other adjustments.  In addition, the Company believes such a reconciliation would imply a degree of precision and certainty that could be confusing to  investors.  These items are uncertain, depend on various factors and may have a material impact on our future GAAP results. </FONT></DIV>

var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
